The paper discusses the efficiency of deep learning for hierarchal generative models, which are commonly used in machine learning tasks such as image and speech recognition. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of deep rendering models, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and information theory, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory).
